{
  "question_id": "6ce90345-b4b3-4481-8f08-d376b9fa0291",
  "short_text": "M pattern with *",
  "content": "Given a number `N`, write a program to print the letter **M** of `N` rows with two **Solid Right Angled Triangles** of `N` rows using stars (`*`).\n\n````\n*                     * \n* *                 * * \n* * *             * * * \n* * * *         * * * * \n* * * * *     * * * * * \n* * * * * * * * * * * *\n````\n\n<MultiLineNote>\nThere is a space after every star (`*`).\n</MultiLineNote>\n\n---\n\n#### Input\n\nThe input will be a single line containing an integer representing `N`.\n\n---\n\n#### Output\n\nThe output should be `N` rows containing stars (`*`) as the letter **M** shown in the sample output.\n\n---\n\n#### Explanation\n\nFor example, if the given number is `N = 6`, \n\n- Print the stars (`*`) on **6** rows as shown in the given image.\n\n<Img imageSrc='https://assets.ccbp.in/frontend/content/programming-foundations/cx-mpattern-with-stars.png' widthPercent='90'/>\n\n<MultiLineNote>\n\nIn the given image,\n\n- The Empty box indicates the two spaces (\"&nbsp;&nbsp;\").\n- The Star in box indicates the star and a space (\"* \")\n\n</MultiLineNote>\n\nThe output should be,\n\n````\n*                     * \n* *                 * * \n* * *             * * * \n* * * *         * * * * \n* * * * *     * * * * * \n* * * * * * * * * * * *\n````",
  "question_type": "CODING",
  "content_type": "MARKDOWN",
  "codes": [
    {
      "code_id": "cfb8d364-b884-4e82-90a9-4836c3128fa8",
      "code_content": "no_of_rows = int(input())\n\nfor each_number in range(1, no_of_rows + 1):\n    first_triangle_stars = \"* \" * each_number\n    first_triangle_spaces = \"  \" * (no_of_rows - each_number)\n\n    first_triangle = first_triangle_stars + first_triangle_spaces\n    \n    second_triangle_spaces = \"  \" * (no_of_rows - each_number)\n    second_triangle_stars = \"* \" * each_number\n\n    second_triangle = second_triangle_spaces + second_triangle_stars\n\n    print(first_triangle + second_triangle)",
      "language": "PYTHON",
      "default_code": true
    }
  ],
